values: I believe I have figured out my love life. I haven't had a boyfriend since.... errr... well you know. I don't believe that any guy is looking at me or for my type. So I'm starting to believe my destiny is to be single forever. I haven't felt that special something, sure I have my crushes but nothing will ever go anywhere.

Hello my fellow... err... MORTALS!!! This is my only computer outlet right now is Mr. Colagross' computer. My internet providers haven't done the providing yet. I'm sooo pissed because they said they would do it on Sept 1st and that is the day we moved in and now it's Sept 5 and its still not done!! I'm so pissed because there are people who only reach me on the internet!! It's like totally not fair!! grr!

Next... Yea. I moved. I'm now more north cape coral than cape coral. I like it though because there aren't as many people than where we were. Plus no one goes down the street we're at like 60 mph. Its kid and dog safe! Though we're like out in the middle of no where. That's okay. I probably still have to pick my friends up if they want to come over. They don't know they way to meh house!! -_-;

So.. school... uh... It's Tuesday and I brought money for pizza and there was none. I was like.. uh.. hello! If it happens tomorrow... there's something wrong with that. I think they should've made some kind of announcement saying there will be no pizza on Tuesday!! I mean seriously. The only reason there was that many people in line was because they brought money for pizza and nothing else so they needed something to eat. Now... on the topic of Ms. Whale. She is like... so easily side tracked she's worse than Mrs J. Mrs J was totally awesomest and we still got some learning in so we weren't completely wasting time away. Ms. Rogers just keeps going with the topic wanting to know everyone's opinion on the matter. Like today, we talked about Steve Irwin dying (The "Crikey" guy). We talked about that the whole class while doing our Words to Own, but there wasn't that many words that we were busy for long. So we talked about the Crikey guy the whole time after the journal. Which I did with one sentence basically. Yearbook. My theme idea wasn't taken but that is okay. I came up with the cover! BAM BABY! We're doing the iPod thing for the cover. If you can't visualize the yearbook as an iPod then come talk to me I have a sketch. It'll be sooooo cool and everyone pretty much liked it over someone elses idea with a guitar. Sooooo... yea. That is all for now.
Remember, I can only use Colagross' compie til my internet provider starts providing such. 

DISH NETWORK RULES!
INVADER ZIM KICKS ASSSSS!!!!!!!!!
Boo YA!
Love always,
Cloud aka Cassie

Grrr...  this week has been total shit! Saturday I almost get run over. Sunday was okay but i had nothing to do and it's sunday. Monday, my uncle died. Tuesday i didnt go to school but me and my brother got into an argument and he totally has no clue how much me and my mom care. Then i also found out that i almost got run over for nothing! Wednesday.. let me just say Ms. Rogers is totally insane and a <strike>bitch</strike> WHALE! err it like grr! Now today we had benchmarks and we only did the science and the PSAT. which i stop in the middle of because i was freezing my ass off and i was falling asleep while reading the questions! I cant believe they make you go through that torture just to get into a good college! the only reason people are getting low scores is because they're falling asleep trying to take it.. or they're just really reallly dumb!

Yup. I would say this week totally sucks. Oh plus, one of my best friends boyfriend (who i was friends with also) broke up and now he isn't my friend anymore. He went for some unattractive unflattering sophomore! what a dumbfuck.

So, it's been the first 'week' of school. I guess it would be considered a week, even though we started on Tuesday. So, I found out my classes. Somehow I got into Pre-Cal but I'm going to try it out. I don't want to give up and be like, I could've done that. Plus, if I fail, I always have business math. Though they're saying if you have more than one math and taking that class it's counting as an elective credit and not a math one. Whatever.

Business math has actually been pretty fun so far. We're doing it like a business so we get to bring in stuff and sell it to our class mates and make money and we have to keep a sheet and it's awesomest. I plan on bringing in Donuts if I can get here early enough *coughdadcough* lol. 

Chemistry.. well nothing has really happened yet to say anything about it... so... next.

English III Honors. OMGAWD! Ms. Rogers. The lady from BOston. She is loud, and insane. I do NOT want to be in her class when there is a fire going on. That entire class would be burn alive and dead. She will still have us lined up against the wall and that is where you'll see the bones of the students bodies!!!!!! Geeze-us!

Pre-Calculus, haha. Vitale! He is the coolest teacher I've had so far this year. I made his oh-so-enthusiastic signs at the end of the year last year. So far it's been review and easy. I know it's going to get harder and when it does hopefully Mr. V will be around so I can get some HELP!

American History. Kossmann is hilarious!! So far his lectures have been fun! He keeps it interesting so you dont fall asleep easily. His favorite phrase today. "Greeeaaaaaat." *sarcastic hint*

French. I am now Colette. That is my french name. Je m'appelle Colette, et to?
lol.

Multimedia Tech. We have done like nothing so far, but draw and color and a crossword puzzle. That is it. nothing else. Lopez is kind of crazy when it comes to certain things *coughpencilsharpenercough*

I'm so bored and thought it was about time to update.

So yesturday, I got my braces off!! YAY!!! I was so happy i couldn't stop smiling. Then I got to get Subway which is always good!! Also, My bottom retainer started to hurt like a mother fucker! It continued to hurt, and I have an appointment tomorrow to get it fixed and I dont have to wear it today. I'm worried my teeth will move but my bottom teeth weren't that crooked to begin with, i think... i dont know. whatever.

 Today I plan on going up to the school and do the whole uniform thing. I should be there the whole time because i think I'll be helping. Hopefully it's not with money cause i suck at change. I figured this out last year. haha. I'm hoping to see some friends of mine there. I misses them alot!!

I went to the movies on Sunday and saw CLERKS II and it was sooooo fucking funny!! You guys should see it! It's so funny!! You don't have to see the first one to see this one, but it does help! 

SCHOOL IS STARTING SOON!!! AHHHHHHHHHHH!!! i'm so ready, though!

So I went to a baseball game yesturday. Miracles vs. Reds. It was definitely interesting. Like... first off we left late and had to wait in traffic to park. That's about the only waiting we did in the beginning. So we got to our seats and no one was next to me for a while and then this is where the fun started. The people who sat next to me were drunks. They were drunk before they got to their seats and they had more beers. So they kept leaving during the game which was fine for me because they took up too much space. They were def rednecks but from New York. My mommy says that there are rednecks up north. Whatever... in the end they got ingaged. We were happy for them. We clapped. and they were cool. They left in like the 7th inning.. There was this cute guy who was like 2 rows behind me. He was def cute. I liked his smile. it was adorable. Though at the beginning i said i wasn't going to be enthusastic about the game that changed after a pepsi. Sugar high, man. The manager told the pitcher to walk this one guy and the bases were loaded and then the next hitter hit a grand slam. I thought that was hilarious and then the pitcher got taken out and some guy in the crowd behind me yelled. "Keep him in, we like him!" we all laughed. It was funny. I think that was the interesting/best game ive ever been too. drunken couple gets engaged cute guy only 2 rows behind me GRAND SLAM! and fireworks!
